5 days work
Discretionary bonus
13-21 days annual leave
Marriage leave
Compassionate leave
Medical insurance
Dental scheme
WFH policy
Unlimited snacks and drinks provided
Periodic tea time gathering
Staff team building activities
and more...

Duties: The appointee will be responsible for performing high-quality analyses, conducting research and overseeing the timely delivery of quality outcomes for internal and external projects, developing value propositions and presenting to relevant committees, sharing on best international practices related to examinations, assessments and research, giving expert advice to Secretariat staff and other parties, and helping the Division Head oversee the smooth running of the Division with the objective of enhancing organizational practices and processes within the human and financial resources given.

Requirements:

A doctoral degree in Education, Statistics, Measurement and Assessment or related disciplines;
At least 6 years of managerial experience, preferably in management of research work;
Abundant knowledge of research concepts and methods;
Substantial knowledge of statistical tools and assessment technology;
Familiarity with multidimensional item response theory and/or cognitive diagnostic modeling is preferred;
Excellent analytical skills and professional report writing skills;
Outstanding presentation and communication skills in Cantonese, English, and Putonghua;
Experience in working with primary and/or secondary schools in Hong Kong is an advantage;
Good interpersonal skills and teamwork spirit; and
Candidates with less working experience will also be considered.

Employment Terms:  The remuneration package will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.  Appointment will be on a fixed-term contract with contract-end-gratuity, MPF benefits, medical and dental care.  Future employment may be offered on renewable contracts subject to performance and staffing needs.

Date for Application Review: 28 January 2022

Applications would be considered until the post is filled.

Application forms can be obtained from the HKEAA office on 13/F., Southorn Centre, 130 Hennessy Road, Wan Chai, Hong Kong or downloaded from the HKEAA website (www.hkeaa.edu.hk/tc/Career/general.html).  Completed application forms should be returned to the Manager – Human Resources at the above address. Due to the secrecy nature of HKEAA's job duties, applicants invited for interview may be required to make a declaration of any conflict of interests. Applicants not notified within 10 weeks from the application review date should consider their applications unsuccessful.

The HKEAA is an equal opportunities employer and welcomes applications from all qualified candidates. Information provided relating to employment will be kept confidential and used only for processing applications. For details, please refer to the Policy Statement on Equal Opportunities and the Personal Information Collection Statement on the HKEAA website (www.hkeaa.edu.hk).

A Manager / Assistant Manager, Laboratory Administration & Compliance is now required as a result of business growth:
Responsibilities:
Responsible for all laboratory management related activities, including equipment re-allocation & disposal, and chemical & clinical wastes disposal;
Maintain routine laboratory operations, including equipment maintenance & calibration, inventory taking and laboratory record maintenance;
Plan and execute quality control assignment on various research & development activities;
Perform risk assessment of operations and evaluate adequacy of internal controls;
Carry out reviews and investigations, provide findings and recommendations to operation teams and top management;
Timely follow up the implementation of recommendations / corrective action plans;
Deliver trainings on integrity and compliance and share of audit requirements to team members;
Assist in laboratory accreditation application and implementation of standard operating procedures;
Liaise with team members and internal audit department on quality matters.
 Requirements:
A degree or above in Science, Engineering or related disciplines;
A minimum of 5 years’ relevant experience, some exposure of regulatory compliance / audit in academia or industry is desirable;
Hands-on experience in laboratory operation and equipment management is preferable;
Proficient in various aspects of laboratory management, including laboratory building services, electrical and mechanical services, laboratory safety, principle, regulation, compliance and ISO international standards;
Self-motivated and team oriented with problem solving ability and excellent documentation skills;
Proficient in both written and spoken English and Chinese; 
Candidates with less experience will be considered for Assistant Manager role.
Thank you for your interest in a career with CK Life Sciences. Competitive compensation and benefits package will be offered to the right candidate. We operate a 5-day workweek, and our benefits cover retirement, health and life. Regular shuttle bus service is also provided with pick-ups and drop-offs at designated and convenient locations. 
To apply for our position, you should write, enclosing a current resume to Chief Manager, Human Resources & Administration, CK Life Sciences Limited, 2 Dai Fu Street, Tai Po Industrial Estate, Hong Kong or by clicking the APPLY NOW button. For more company information, please visit www.ck-lifesciences.com. 
We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates.  Personal data collected will be treated in strictest confidence and handled confidentially by authorized personnel for recruitment-related purposes within the Group.

Responsibilities

Participate in BioRadar related R&D projects;
Perform laboratory tests and data analysis independently by strictly following the standard operation procedures. Conduct experiments including nucleic acid extraction, PCR and quantitative PCR, isothermal amplification, DNA cloning, bacterial culture, bio-chip examination, etc.. Complete the research tasks assigned by supervisor;
Report experimental results, progressions and arising problems to supervisor routinely;
Carry out method development, optimization and validation under the supervision of R&D director;
Lab organizational duties such as sourcing of laboratory consumables, preparation of reagents and buffers, calibration and daily maintenance of laboratory instrumentation  related documentation.
Perform other duties as assigned.

Requirements

Higher Diploma  or above in molecular biology, microbiology, biochemistry, or other biotech-related disciplines;
Hands-on experience in basic  molecular bio-techniques including nucleic acid extraction and PCR
Mature, responsible, independent, career-minded and able to work under pressure;
Familiar with GLP or ISO regulations is a plus;Good command in both verbal and written Chinese and English
Relevant working experience preferred;

If you are passionate, driven and looking for a new and exciting opportunity within a successful and growing company, this may be the right role for you.

Please click “Apply Now” to submit your application.

All Personal data collected will be strictly confidential and used for recruitment purpose only. Applicants who are not invited to an interview within one month from the closing date should consider their applications unsuccessful. If you are not selected, all data will be destroyed within six months from the date you applied.

Objective

Reporting to Assistant Technical Manager, you will work closely with your team and the other departments to support their needs. The job would be focus on consolidation work to technical documentation.

Responsibilities

Maintain technical documents for internal use or for client distribution. Documents include standards and regulation, internal interpretation and policies, testing protocols, and other technical related documentation;
Routine project handling supporting task;
Assist any other related duties as assigned.
Job requirements

Secondary school level of education or above;
Familiar with /knowledge of ISO 17025 and accreditations requirement is preferred;
Able to work 3 days or above is preferred;
1-2 years working experience is preferred;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese;
Proficiency in MS office Suite and general computer skills.

[Work Location: Science Park, Shatin]

Reporting to the Research Manager, the appointee will be required to:

be responsible for planning the overall project, conducting research works and achieving the project deliverables;
manage R&D projects, including technical and financial aspects and other project administrative tasks, such as preparing project updates and reports;
work closely with R&D researchers and personnel; coordinate with local and overseas universities, research institutions and business partners, and handle enquiries in a professional manner; and
perform any other duties as assigned.

 Requirements:

a bachelor’s degree or above in Material Science, Chemistry, Chemical Engineering, Apparel/Textile Technology, Textile Chemistry or Textile Engineering; a postgraduate degree in these disciplines would be an advantage but not a must;
4 or more years of research/ relevant work experience;
highly-organized and capable of working under pressure with multi-task assignments;
good interpersonal skills; and
fluent in both written and spoken English and Chinese, with good command of Putonghua being an advantage.

Applicants should state their current and expected salary in the application. Salary offered will be commensurate with qualifications and experience. Appointment will be offered on a contract basis, re-engagement thereafter is subject to mutual agreement.

Applicants are invited to send detailed curriculum vitae in strict confidence to Human Resources Manager, HKRITA, R906-8, Shirley Chan Building, The Hong Kong Polytechnic University, Hung Hom, Kowloon. Recruitment will continue until the position is filled. HKRITA reserves the right to consider late applications and nominations, and to fill or not to fill the positions. Personal data provided by applicants will be used for recruitment and other employment-related purpose.

Please mark “PRIVATE & CONFIDENTIAL” and quote the position applied for and its reference number on the envelope.

DEPARTMENT OF COMPUTING

Postdoctoral Fellow / Research Associate (Ref.22011203)

[Appointment period: twelve to thirty-six months]

Duties

The appointee will assist the project leader in the research project - “Second phase of the Jockey Club diversity at schools project”.  The project aims to transform local schools into self‐learning organizations that are capable to manage student diversity effectively and efficiently in their school-based contexts through the development and enhancement of school‐based diversity infrastructures in three domains: data‐driven / data‐informed school practice, learning and teaching activities, and close collaboration.  He/She will act as AI Solution Engineer and be required to:

(a) carry out software development tasks to develop appropriate solutions for student data processing and analytics using AI technology for prediction and intervention for diversity management and appropriate profiling, reporting, analytics and intervention;

(b) develop appropriate trainings to enable adoption and cultivation of a data usage culture in the education sector;

(c) identify, collect and analyze system requirements;

(d) establish appropriate system and data architecture, information flow and processes;

(e) conduct design, analysis and software development to design appropriate and reliable solutions;

(f) assist in the development of appropriate trainings for schools, teachers and systems administrators to facilitate adoption and use of the data platform and related solutions;

(g) maintain and support software, resolve any issues or problems, and ensure reliable and secure services;

(h) ensure any incidents/problems being timely and satisfactorily resolved;

(i) prepare appropriate documentation and operations procedures to support usage;

(j) review system performance and the performance of service providers (if any);

(k) participate in regular project team meetings;

(l) collect feedback from users/other project teams, consolidate enhancement suggestions and channels to appropriate teams;

(m) report progress, follow up outstanding issues with all related parties; suggest solutions and address problems, and escalating key issues and problems; and

(n) assist in systems testing to ensure quality systems and services.

Qualifications

For the post of Postdoctoral Fellow, applicants should have a doctoral degree or an equivalent qualification and must have no more than five years of post‐qualification experience at the time of application.

For the posts of Research Associate, applicants should have a master’s degree or a good honours degree with three or more years of research/relevant work experience.

For both posts, applicants should also:

(a) have at least 3 years’ experience in software engineering, preferably with some project management experience;

(b) have good communications skills and be fluent in both written and spoken English and Chinese; and

(c) have knowledge of and experience in AI, big data, analytics, use of BI tools, and application of IT in education.

Preference will be given to those with postgraduate qualification in advance technology (e.g. AI), and familiarity in school environment and use of data in education.

Applicants are invited to contact Prof. Jiannong Cao at tel no. 2766 7275, fax no. 2744 0842 or email via "Apply Now" for further information.

Remuneration

A highly competitive remuneration package will be offered.  Applicants should state their current and expected salary in the application.

Application

Please send a completed application form by post to Human Resources Office, 13/F, Li Ka Shing Tower, The Hong Kong Polytechnic University, Hung Hom, Kowloon, Hong Kong or via email by clicking "Apply Now".  Application forms can be downloaded from  https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/forms. If a separate curriculum vitae is to be provided, please still complete the application form which will help speed up the recruitment process.  The closing date for application is Thursday, 10 February 2022.  Applicants who are not invited to an interview within two months from the closing date should consider their applications unsuccessful.  Applications should be addressed directly to Prof. Jiannong Cao (please state Department ofComputing on the envelope).  The University’s Personal Information Collection Statement for recruitment can be found at https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/pics_for_recruitment.

PolyU is an equal opportunity employer committed to diversity and inclusivity.  All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to gender, ethnicity, nationality, family status or physical or mental disabilities.
